body:
Hi, new to Verilator (and Verilog in general) so this might be a FAQ, but Verilator is generating the SystemC model `Vcounter` from my SystemVerilog mode `counter` with mismatched port width.  The width of `count_o` in `counter.sv` is 8 bits, but in `Vcounter.h` it is 32 bits.  Is this expected?  Any way to force Verilator to keep the exact number of bits defined in the SystemVerilog model?

```
module counter #(
    parameter int WIDTH = 8
) (
    input  logic             arst_ni,
    input  logic             clk_i,
    input  logic             up_i,
    output logic [WIDTH-1:0] count_o
);

  always_ff @(posedge clk_i or negedge arst_ni) begin
    if (~arst_ni) begin
      count_o <= 3;
    end else begin
      if (up_i) begin
        count_o <= count_o + 1;
      end else begin
        count_o <= count_o - 1;
      end
    end
  end

  function automatic logic [WIDTH-1:0] read();
    return count_o;
  endfunction

endmodule
```
